<br>
Keniden Swrath<br>
31 Half-Elf Warrior<br>
Tenkei <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usarmaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarmaldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/01 7:05:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1HS v 2HS</span><hr size=1> Well, I guess that is a personal call. At lvl 51, I keep aggro better with two weapons, and the faster the better. When Im not the main tank, or the mob has a shitty damage shield that the caster won't dispel (wake him up!), I use a 2-hander. <br>
<br>
Being a warrior, I have the strength required to carry more than the weapons Im using. I generally keep one of each type with me.<br>
<br>
The reason I do that is because when Im in game, I consider myself a Man-at-Arms, a muscle for hire, etc. It is my &quot;job&quot; to be good in all skills so I like to practice them all. To me, there is nothing more annoying than a warrior that admires a nice weapon you have, then when you offer to let him/her try it, the say &quot;My skill is 14&quot; PFFFT....that's what palidans and shadow knights say. One day, I'll even be in a raid and we will be kicking ass and I'll train up hand to hand even...why not? Fightings what we do. Did you ever talk to a druid or wizard that had all the teleport spells except North Karnana because &quot;they don't use it.&quot; Or a cleric who doesn't complete heal because &quot;they just use superior healing&quot;<br>
<br>
Main point, you don't have to make up yuor mind now. You should keep all skills high. You might actually find yourself winning a kick-ass 2 hander and then use that money you were saving for the most important thing a warrior needs....ARMOR.<br>
<br>
